gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 135, Nuggets 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings snapped a two-game skid as they defeated the Nuggets, 135-106. Domantas Sabonis led the Kings with his league-leading 16th triple-double of the season with 17 points, 17 rebounds, and 10 assists, he has now recorded four triple-doubles in his last six games and eight in the last 13 games. Malik Monk added 23 points while DeAaron Fox totaled 15 points and 10 assists. Nikola Jokic led the Nuggets with 23 points, eight rebounds, and seven assists. The Kings improve to 30-21 as the Nuggets move to 36-17.
